<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n33229g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n33" href="#n33229g">N33 (VI.B.4)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n33all.htm#n33229g"> 229(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> ~ chigoe</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Linnaeus (1758) only mentions two species of flea: the human flea which he appropriately names <i>Pulex irritans</i>, and the <mark>chigoe</mark> of hot countries which he called <i>Pulex penetrans</i>, from the habit which the female has of burrowing under the skin of her victims. <small> Harold Russell, <a name="HRTF" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#HRTF"><cite title="source">The Flea</cite></a> (1913) 4</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: chigoe flea = jigger</mm> </dd></dl>
